I"£<p>Although RubyMotion is great, sometimes is hard to know how to use some Cocoa methods or parameters. This is how you translate an action parameter <strong>(SEL)action</strong>:</p>

<div class="language-objc highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="n">UIBarButtonItem</span> <span class="o">*</span><span class="n">refreshButton</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[[</span><span class="n">UIBarButtonItem</span> <span class="nf">alloc</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="nf">initWithBarButtonSystemItem</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="n">UIBarButtonSystemItemRefresh</span> 
                                                          <span class="nl">target:</span><span class="n">self</span> 
                                                          <span class="nl">action:</span><span class="k">@selector</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">refreshMeasures</span><span class="p">)];</span>
</code></pre></div></div>
<p><br /></p>

<div class="language-ruby highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="n">refreshButton</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="no">UIBarButtonItem</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nf">alloc</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nf">initWithBarButtonSystemItem</span><span class="p">(</span>
      <span class="no">UIBarButtonSystemItemRefresh</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">target</span><span class="ss">:self</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">action</span><span class="ss">:'refreshMeasures'</span><span class="p">)</span>    
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>where <em>refreshMeasures</em> is a method defined in the class</p>

<div class="language-ruby highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">refreshMeasures</span>
<span class="k">end</span>
</code></pre></div></div>
